# Development Workflow

## Before every commit
```bash
npm run check        # tsc --noEmit + next lint (must pass)
npm run build        # must produce exit code 0
```

## After writing a new migration file
```bash
npm run migrate      # supabase db push (requires CLI linked)
npm run types        # regenerate src/types/supabase-generated.ts
npm run check        # verify no type drift
```

## After changing schema types
Update `src/types/database.ts` to match. Then run `npm run check`.

## Cache reset (after large file rewrites during hot reload)
```bash
npm run reset-cache  # rm -rf .next
# then restart: npm run dev
```

## Commit conventions
```
feat(scope): add wholesale order tracking
fix(scope): guard zero-commission trigger
chore(scope): add migration 008 delivery fee
```
Scopes: `auth`, `products`, `orders`, `wholesale`, `affiliate`, `admin`, `schema`, `ui`, `deps`

## Migration naming
```
NNN_short_descriptive_name.sql   # e.g. 008_delivery_fee_and_costs.sql
```
Always idempotent. Never drop columns. Never destroy data.

## Environment variables
- Local dev: `.env.local` (gitignored, never commit)
- Production: set in Vercel dashboard
- Reference: `.env.production.example` (committed, no real values)

## Supabase CLI commands (after install + link)
```bash
supabase db push                           # apply pending migrations
supabase gen types typescript \
  --project-id owvtfzxvirttrbcsiveg \
  --schema public > src/types/supabase-generated.ts
supabase db diff                           # preview schema diff
```

## Deployment
Push to `main` → GitHub Actions CI runs → if green, Vercel auto-deploys.
Never deploy manually unless CI is broken.

## Debugging runtime errors
1. Read terminal output file in `.cursor/projects/.../terminals/`
2. Fix the code
3. `npm run check` to verify
4. If ENOENT manifest error → `npm run reset-cache` then restart dev server
